      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence errors and floating-point round-off contributions to QoI uncertainty must be quantified and shown to be negligible relative to discretization error.",
      "rationale": "Solver iterative convergence was monitored via residual norms but no formal quantification of numerical solver error contribution to QoI was performed. This factor was not assessed due to resource constraints and schedule pressure."
