      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Uncertainty in model input parameters (geometry tolerances, fluid properties, boundary conditions) must be propagated to quantify their contribution to QoI uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Sensitivity analysis performed for ±5% variation in inlet flow rate, hematocrit, and rotational speed. Combined input uncertainty contribution to NIH is 6.8%, documented and within acceptable bounds."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Variability in experimental test samples (blood analogue fluid batches, pump unit-to-unit geometric variation) must be characterized and its effect on validation data assessed.",
      "rationale": "Experimental data sourced from the FDA benchmark dataset does not include unit-to-unit geometric variability characterization or batch-to-batch fluid property variation. No supplementary sample variability study was conducted. Factor not assessed."
